
                                            Robin Wade, aged 31, was gunned down inside his vehicle on Thursday.
                                         CAPE TOWN - Police have launched an investigation into the murder of a taxi driver in Steenberg. Robin Wade, aged 31, was gunned down inside his vehicle on Thursday. He sustained a gunshot wound to the head. The motive for the attack is unclear. The police's Sinathi Joni says that they’re investigating. “The man was fatally wounded as a result of the shooting. A murder case has been registered for investigation.” Joni says the suspects remain at large. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)